Pre-Coding Technical Checklist for SUDS

You're already in good shape with the DB schema , feature blueprint , and file structure . Here's what to lock down before writing a single line of code:
✅ 1. Finalize Your DB Schema

    Confirm all relationships (FKs, joins) are correct
    Confirm the services JSON fields have a defined shape — don't leave those vague
    Add any missing tables (e.g., reviews, messages/threads, subscriptions, notifications)
    Decide on Row Level Security (RLS) rules if using Supabase

✅ 2. Auth Flow Decision

    Email/password + social login (Google, Facebook) 
    Decide on session handling (JWT, Supabase Auth, etc.)
    Map out the full auth flow: sign up → profile creation → role selection (customer vs provider)

✅ 3. API / Data Layer Contract

    For every screen in your file structure , define what data it needs and where it comes from
    Write out your key Supabase queries and mutations before building UI (these live in lib/supabase/queries.ts and mutations.ts)
    Define your Stripe integration points: one-time deposit (15%), recurring billing for subscriptions 

✅ 4. Define Your Type System

    Fill out types/models.ts and types/supabase.ts based on your schema 
    Every entity (User, Booking, Provider, Service, Review) should have a typed interface before you touch a component

 5. Design Tokens & Theme

    Lock in your color scheme, typography, spacing in design/theme.ts and tokens.ts 
    This prevents design drift once you start building components

 6. Map MVP User Flows (screen by screen)

Based on Phase 1 priority , trace these end-to-end before coding:

    Customer flow: Search → Filter → Provider Profile → Book → Payment → Confirmation
    Provider flow: Onboarding → Set services → Accept/decline bookings → View calendar
    Auth flow: Register → Add vehicle → Add payment method

 7. Third-Party Services — Accounts & Config Ready

Before coding, have these set up:

    Stripe — account created, test keys ready, webhook endpoints planned
    Supabase — project created, schema migrated, storage buckets configured
    Push notifications — Expo push or similar configured
    Geolocation — decide on provider (Google Maps API, etc.) and have keys ready

 8. State Management Plan

Your file structure has state/auth.ts, state/search.ts, state/bookingDraft.ts  — before coding, decide:

    What lives in global state vs local component state
    How the booking draft gets built step-by-step across screens

 9. Error & Edge Case Handling Plan

Specifically for SUDS:

    What happens if a booking is cancelled within 24 hrs (deposit forfeited)  — define the logic clearly
    What triggers a blocked message in the inbox (phone, email, Venmo mentions) 
    What happens if a provider rejects a booking?

 10. Dev Environment & Tooling

    ESLint, Prettier, TypeScript config locked in
    Branching strategy decided (e.g., main, dev, feature branches)
    Testing approach decided (even if minimal for MVP)